> This Roasted Pepper and Aubergine Linguine with Diced Chorizo is bursting full of flavours and makes the perfect dinner night option from HelloFresh. Cook up a fresh start!

== Roasted Vegetables ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the pasta.

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then cut into roughly 2cm pieces.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm pieces.

Pop both veg onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf until soft, ~{15-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Pasta ==

While the veg roasts, add the @linguine{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Pine Nuts and Chives ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped) (use scissors if easier).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @pine nuts{15%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Transfer the pine nuts to a #bowl{} and set aside.

== Sauce ==

Pop your pan back on medium heat and add a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @finely chopped tomatoes{1%can}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce. Season with @salt{}/ and @black pepper{}.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Once cooked, combine the roasted veg, cooked pasta and sauce in whichever pan is the largest.

Stir in half the chives and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Add a splash more water if it seems a bit dry.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed.

== Serving ==

When everything is ready, serve your roasted pepper and aubergine linguine in #bowls{}.

Finish with the pine nuts and a sprinkling of the remaining chives and cheese. Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you've chosen to add chorizo to your meal, add @chorizo{90%g}(diced) to the pan before you add the garlic and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and continue with the recipe as instructed.